<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-326-444  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 326 444.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>MacWEEK  June 6 1989 v3 n22 p6(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT MacWEEK Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IPSS puts demographics on Mac. (Interactive Population StatisticalSystem) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Perrow, Jonathan.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   PSRC Software (product introduction).andO;Product:   Interactive Population Statistical System (computer Program)(product introduction).andO;Topic:     DemographyStatistical SoftwareProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IPSS puts demographics on MacandM;Bowling Green, Ohio.andP;  -- PSRC Software has begun shippin a demographicstatistics and simulation package that puts the power of populationprojections into the hands of researchers, planners and educators.andM;The graphics-based Interactive Population Statistical System, or IPSS, is a$295 Macintosh application that the company claims is easier to use and morepowerful than any other demographics program available for a personalcomputer.andM;The program can be used, for example, by market researchers to plot changesin variables such as births, deaths, infant mortality rate, fertility rateand age in a market area and then analyze the implications of such changes onthat market.andM;Data can be pasted in from the Clipboard, automatically entered frompre-prepared schedules, typed in from the keyboard or entered graphicallywith the mouse by drawing the desired function.andM;IPSS can generate two- and three-dimensional color graphs.andP;  &quot;When [IPSS]animates a series of population pyramids as part of a presentation, everyonein the room quickly grasps how the population is changing and what it islikely to do to sales,&quot; said Jerry Wicks, author of the program.andM;IPSS runs on a Mac Plus, SE or II.andP;  A second version, called IPSS+ andoptimized for the 68881 or 68882 math coprocessors used in the Mac II, IIxand IIex, is available for $395.andM;PSRC Software is located on the campus of Bowling Green University, BowlingGreen, Ohio, 43403-0185; (419) 372-2497.andO;</TEXT></DOC>